                                                       Sunday 26 J<uni 70>*
Dear papa

.ue 2
                                                                      $..#$
Forts.: 26 J<uni 70>*
I hope that you could sleep on the way inspite of much talking, I hope far-
ther the catarrh has not return though it is rather cold today at least
here, we had rain yesterday which has coolled much, I regrette that you
have not a warmer coat,

Yesterday Paul felt less well then the day before, the night was as usual,
today he has headach and little fever, The Doctor sounded the woond, found
it rather deep and extended. He thinks also that it will last a pretty long
time, the bone is not affected but it lais very near, <"an einer kleinen
Stelle liegt der Knochen blo·" ->611
